	<p>
		Hi! I'm Bridger Schaffer From Sherwood, Oregon. <br>
		I am currently a Freshman at Embry Riddle Aeronautical University, in Prescott, Arizona. 
		I am majoring in Aeronautical Science, with a long-term goal to become a professional pilot. 
		Additionally, I hope to gain the skills to be put into a business management type of job.
		Since the summer of 2024, I discovered my passion for aviation and flying, and since then, 
		I have gotten my Private Pilot's License, and I am working on my Instrument License. 
	</p>

	<p>
		Outside of my education, I have always loved the outdoors. Growing up in Oregon, 
		I grew a passion for skiing, mountain biking, and hiking. Over the years, I competed with 
		the Southwest Mountain Ski Team. I have visited many national parks including Yosemite, where I 
		summitted Half Dome with some of my family. I completed an adventure race with my dad. Now, in 
		Prescott, Arizona, I hope to see even more of the great outdoors! There is always much more, and
		feel free to contact me if you want to talk more. 
	</p>

